---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms and conditions for using PepCodex. Please read these terms carefully before using our website."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <header class="mb-12 relative">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-[var(--primary)]/10 via-transparent to-transparent rounded-2xl -z-10"></div>
      <div class="p-6">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-xl text-white/80">
          Please read these terms carefully before using PepCodex.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/60">Last updated: January 2026</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
      <!-- Agreement -->
      <section id="agreement">
        <h2>1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or using PepCodex (pepcodex.com, "the Website"), you agree to be bound by
          these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to all of these Terms, you are
          prohibited from using or accessing this Website.
        </p>
        <p>
          These Terms apply to all visitors, users, and others who access or use the Website.
          We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. Your continued use of the
          Website following the posting of revised Terms means you accept and agree to the changes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Description of Service -->
      <section id="description" class="mt-12">
        <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
        <p>
          PepCodex is an educational platform that provides research-based information about
          peptides, synthesized from peer-reviewed scientific literature, clinical trials, and
          regulatory documents.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>The Website provides:</strong>
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Educational content about peptide research</li>
          <li>Summaries and analysis of published scientific studies</li>
          <li>Links to primary research sources</li>
          <li>A glossary of scientific terms</li>
          <li>Newsletter subscription services</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <strong>The Website does NOT provide:</strong>
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment recommendations</li>
          <li>Dosing protocols or usage instructions</li>
          <li>Product recommendations or sourcing information</li>
          <li>Any form of healthcare services</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Educational Purpose -->
      <section id="educational-purpose" class="mt-12">
        <h2>3. Educational Purpose Only</h2>

        <div class="not-prose my-8 rounded-xl border border-[var(--primary)]/30 bg-[var(--primary)]/10 p-6 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-purple-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
              <path d="M12 16v-4"/>
              <path d="M12 8h.01"/>
            </svg>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-purple-300 mb-2">Important Notice</h3>
              <p class="text-white/80">
                All content on PepCodex is for educational and informational purposes only.
                It is not intended to be a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis,
                or treatment.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>
          By using the Website, you acknowledge and agree that:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            The information provided is for general educational purposes only
          </li>
          <li>
            You will not use the information for self-diagnosis or self-treatment
          </li>
          <li>
            You will consult qualified healthcare professionals for any health-related decisions
          </li>
          <li>
            The content does not create a doctor-patient or any other professional relationship
          </li>
          <li>
            You are solely responsible for how you use the information provided
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Please review our full <a href="/disclaimer">Disclaimer</a> for more information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Intellectual Property -->
      <section id="intellectual-property" class="mt-12">
        <h2>4. Intellectual Property Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Unless otherwise indicated, the Website and all content, features, and functionality
          (including but not limited to all information, software, text, displays, images, and
          the design, selection, and arrangement thereof) are owned by PepCodex and are protected
          by copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws.
        </p>

        <h3>Your Use of Content</h3>
        <p>
          You may access and use the Website for your personal, non-commercial, educational use
          only. You may not:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Copy, modify, distribute, sell, or lease any part of the Website or its content
          </li>
          <li>
            Reverse engineer or attempt to extract the source code of any software
          </li>
          <li>
            Use any automated system to access the Website in a manner that sends more requests
            than a human can reasonably produce
          </li>
          <li>
            Remove any copyright, trademark, or other proprietary notices
          </li>
          <li>
            Create derivative works based on the Website content
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Citation and Fair Use</h3>
        <p>
          You may quote brief excerpts from the Website content for educational, commentary,
          or criticism purposes, provided you:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide proper attribution to PepCodex</li>
          <li>Include a link to the original content</li>
          <li>Do not imply endorsement by PepCodex</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- User Conduct -->
      <section id="user-conduct" class="mt-12">
        <h2>5. User Conduct</h2>
        <p>
          By using the Website, you agree NOT to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Use the Website for any unlawful purpose or in violation of any applicable laws
          </li>
          <li>
            Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any portion of the Website or any systems
            or networks connected to the Website
          </li>
          <li>
            Interfere with or disrupt the Website or servers or networks connected to the Website
          </li>
          <li>
            Introduce any viruses, malware, or other harmful code
          </li>
          <li>
            Collect or store personal data about other users
          </li>
          <li>
            Use the Website to transmit spam, chain letters, or other unsolicited communications
          </li>
          <li>
            Impersonate any person or entity or misrepresent your affiliation with a person or entity
          </li>
          <li>
            Use the Website to advertise or offer to sell goods or services
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Third-Party Links -->
      <section id="third-party-links" class="mt-12">
        <h2>6. Third-Party Links and Content</h2>
        <p>
          The Website contains links to third-party websites, including scientific journals,
          research databases, clinical trial registries, and regulatory agencies. These links
          are provided solely for convenience and informational purposes.
        </p>
        <p>
          PepCodex does not:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Control or endorse the content of any third-party website</li>
          <li>Guarantee the accuracy of information on third-party websites</li>
          <li>Accept responsibility for the privacy practices of third-party websites</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You access third-party websites at your own risk and subject to the terms and
          conditions of those websites.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Newsletter -->
      <section id="newsletter" class="mt-12">
        <h2>7. Newsletter and Communications</h2>
        <p>
          If you subscribe to our newsletter:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            You agree to receive periodic emails from PepCodex
          </li>
          <li>
            You can unsubscribe at any time by clicking the unsubscribe link in any email
          </li>
          <li>
            We will handle your email address in accordance with our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            Newsletter content is for informational purposes only and subject to the same
            disclaimers as the Website content
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Disclaimers -->
      <section id="disclaimers" class="mt-12">
        <h2>8. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>
          THE WEBSITE AND ITS CONTENT ARE PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT ANY
          WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED.
        </p>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, PepCodex disclaims all warranties,
          express or implied, including but not limited to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Warranties of merchantability and fitness for a particular purpose</li>
          <li>Warranties of non-infringement</li>
          <li>Warranties that the Website will be uninterrupted, error-free, or secure</li>
          <li>Warranties regarding the accuracy, reliability, or completeness of any content</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          No information obtained from the Website creates any warranty not expressly stated
          in these Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Limitation of Liability -->
      <section id="limitation" class="mt-12">
        <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, PEPCODEX, ITS OWNERS, EMPLOYEES, CONTRIBUTORS,
          AND AFFILIATES SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL,
          OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Loss of profits, data, use, goodwill, or other intangible losses</li>
          <li>Personal injury or property damage resulting from your use of the Website</li>
          <li>
            Any errors, mistakes, or inaccuracies of content
          </li>
          <li>
            Any unauthorized access to or use of our servers or any personal information
          </li>
          <li>
            Any interruption or cessation of transmission to or from the Website
          </li>
          <li>
            Any health decisions or outcomes based on information from the Website
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This limitation of liability applies whether the alleged liability is based on contract,
          tort, negligence, strict liability, or any other basis, even if PepCodex has been advised
          of the possibility of such damage.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Indemnification -->
      <section id="indemnification" class="mt-12">
        <h2>10. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>
          You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless PepCodex, its owners, employees,
          contributors, and affiliates from and against any and all claims, damages, obligations,
          losses, liabilities, costs, or debt, and expenses (including but not limited to
          attorney's fees) arising from:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your use of and access to the Website</li>
          <li>Your violation of any term of these Terms</li>
          <li>
            Your violation of any third-party right, including any intellectual property or
            privacy right
          </li>
          <li>
            Any claim that your use of the Website caused damage to a third party
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Governing Law -->
      <section id="governing-law" class="mt-12">
        <h2>11. Governing Law and Jurisdiction</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the
          United States, without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
        </p>
        <p>
          Any disputes arising out of or relating to these Terms or the Website shall be
          resolved through binding arbitration in accordance with the rules of the American
          Arbitration Association, except that either party may seek injunctive or other
          equitable relief in any court of competent jurisdiction.
        </p>
        <p>
          You agree to waive any right to participate in a class action lawsuit or class-wide
          arbitration.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Severability -->
      <section id="severability" class="mt-12">
        <h2>12. Severability</h2>
        <p>
          If any provision of these Terms is held to be unenforceable or invalid, such provision
          will be changed and interpreted to accomplish the objectives of such provision to the
          greatest extent possible under applicable law, and the remaining provisions will
          continue in full force and effect.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Waiver -->
      <section id="waiver" class="mt-12">
        <h2>13. Waiver</h2>
        <p>
          The failure of PepCodex to enforce any right or provision of these Terms will not be
          considered a waiver of those rights. The waiver of any such right or provision will
          be effective only if in writing and signed by a duly authorized representative of
          PepCodex.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Entire Agreement -->
      <section id="entire-agreement" class="mt-12">
        <h2>14. Entire Agreement</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms, together with the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>,
          <a href="/disclaimer">Disclaimer</a>, <a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>,
          and any other legal notices published by PepCodex on the Website, constitute the
          entire agreement between you and PepCodex concerning the Website.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Changes -->
      <section id="changes" class="mt-12">
        <h2>15. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right, at our sole discretion, to modify or replace these Terms at
          any time. If a revision is material, we will provide at least 30 days' notice prior
          to any new terms taking effect.
        </p>
        <p>
          What constitutes a material change will be determined at our sole discretion. By
          continuing to access or use the Website after any revisions become effective, you
          agree to be bound by the revised terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <section id="contact" class="mt-12">
        <h2>16. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us:
        </p>
        <p>
          Email: <a href="mailto:legal@pepcodex.com">legal@pepcodex.com</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Related Pages -->
      <section id="related" class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-white/10">
        <h2>Related Legal Pages</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/disclaimer">Disclaimer</a></li>
          <li><a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="/fda-notice">FDA Notice</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
